NAME
    WordList::Test::Number::1Million - 1 million numbers from "0000001" to
    "1000000"

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of
    WordList::Test::Number::1Million (from Perl distribution
    WordList-Test-Number-1Million), released on 2018-04-02.

SYNOPSIS
     use WordList::Test::Number::1Million;

     my $wl = WordList::Test::Number::1Million->new;

     # Pick a (or several) random word(s) from the list
     my $word = $wl->pick;
     my @words = $wl->pick(3);

     # Check if a word exists in the list
     if ($wl->word_exists('foo')) { ... }

     # Call a callback for each word
     $wl->each_word(sub { my $word = shift; ... });

     # Get all the words
     my @all_words = $wl->all_words;

STATISTICS
     +----------------------------------+---------+
     | key                              | value   |
     +----------------------------------+---------+
     | avg_word_len                     | 7       |
     | longest_word_len                 | 7       |
     | num_words                        | 1000000 |
     | num_words_contains_nonword_chars | 0       |
     | num_words_contains_unicode       | 0       |
     | num_words_contains_whitespace    | 0       |
     | shortest_word_len                | 7       |
     +----------------------------------+---------+

    The statistics is available in the %STATS package variable.

